body: @SummerOfServenteen @kezhenxu94 Please review #2931

https://github.com/apache/skywalking/blob/fa7a1983f9be13280a3d5842a6b99d6b5c43563a/apm-sniffer/apm-agent-core/src/main/java/org/apache/skywalking/apm/agent/core/context/util/ThrowableTransformer.java#L50

This is a weird line @wu-sheng
Why get the cause for deeper stack is weird? In this case, they create a self-ref, which cause OOM only.
Looks like the same ```throwable``` is returning
Good catch. That is a bug. I will fix that.

> @wu-sheng why this builds fails, it tells me that other pkg's class is not allowed.

Yes, importing third parties' class will break the agent when there is no such class in the target application, see #2871 and #2908 , and never try to use full qualified class names to work around the failure, use string literature if needed

> I know you don't support 5.0.8.RELEASE version now. Do you have plans to support other versions of webflux in the future?

Plugins developed and contributed for different frameworks and different versions, but it only comes from the community. Some contributors think one version is valuable to support, they could follow our development document, PR review, integration tests, in order to make it merged into the main repo. Like all these plugins you saw.
In SkyWalking, we are totally community-based and community-driven. So some new version supports require everyone like you to contribute.

But I found `spring-webflux_5.0.8.RELEASE-spring-mvc_5.0.8.RELEASE` in the test case, maybe there is some bugs, could you submit a new demo to help on reproducing this error?

The same question, if you don't need it, just don't attach the agent to JVM.

Are you asking severl web apps in one Tomcat container? Some are monitoring targets, others are not? I am just guessing because you don't give me a very clear context.
No update in one month.
Bootstrap loader is more complex than this. I will remove it from this PR.

I have a quick read about line cache, fail share and disruptor articles.
Now I could understand why this could be quicker. But I am not sure all codes, still a little hard about static block.
The thing I am still thinking about is the sun.unsafe incompatible risk. I was facing disruptor incompatible issue in IBM j9vm.

I will go to Shanghai KubeCon to give a talk. So, may be a little late.
Merged. @SummerOfServenteen Could you try the master branch?

> I have a quick read about line cache, fail share and disruptor articles.
> Now I could understand why this could be quicker. But I am not sure all codes, still a little hard about static block.
> The thing I am still thinking about is the sun.unsafe incompatible risk. I was facing disruptor incompatible issue in IBM j9vm.
> 
> I will go to Shanghai KubeCon to give a talk. So, may be a little late.

Yes, sun.unsafe is not safe, I'm thinking about a better solution.
In java 8 we can use annotation Contended to solve the false-sharing problem, but in java 7 or lower version may got a compile error.
could you please tell me what's the time of your next publication?
I hope I could froze codes next week.
I and my co-worker tried to package a few days ago, but it always failed and  he had said that in qq group 2

How fail? There are many messages every day. I can't follow all.
CI checked package for every merge. Should be fine.

@wu-sheng I'm pushed the code  using an AtomicIntegerArray with 31 continuous integer instead of AtomicInteger to solve the false-sharing problem and it didn't use sun.unsafe directly.
So I think it's a better solution, what's your opinion?
